WEBVTT

00:10:29.231 --> 00:10:32.333
we've told our children
that manufacturing had no future.

00:10:32.357 --> 00:10:34.334
That it was something happening far away.

00:10:34.358 --> 00:10:36.156
We need to reverse that

00:10:36.180 --> 00:10:38.576
and teach manufacturing again
at university.

00:10:39.203 --> 00:10:42.688
Only the countries
that will boldly transform

00:10:42.712 --> 00:10:44.734
will be able to seize this growth.

00:10:46.640 --> 00:10:49.507
It's also a chance
for developing economies.

00:10:50.461 --> 00:10:54.094
Of course China
and other emerging economies

00:10:54.118 --> 00:10:56.218
won't be the factory of the world anymore.

00:10:57.545 --> 00:11:02.163
Actually, it was not a sustainable
model in the long term,